        <td colspan="2">
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Top-Tip:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">If there are many Dyads in the model, you can use the Kinematics-Tree to help you identify each Dyad.</para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">In the Kinematics-Tree</para>
          <list id="8" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Numbered" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-style:normal;">Click and explore the </text><text styleclass="Interface" style="font-style:normal;">Kinematics-Tree</text><text styleclass="VariableName" style="font-style:normal;">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Numbered"><text style="font-style:normal;">Click each</text>&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">The <text styleclass="Element">Parts</text> and <text styleclass="Element">Joints</text> of each <text styleclass="VariableName">Dyad</text> become <text styleclass="VariableName" style="color:#ff0000;">red</text> in the <text styleclass="Interface">graphic-area</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
